---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Programs | Imagination Grove Academy" description="IGA's age-appropriate programs for children 6 weeks through 5 years. Small class sizes, degree-qualified lead teachers, and curriculum that meets your child where they are.">

    <!-- ========== HERO ========== -->
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">Programs at IGA</p>
          <h1>A program for every stage of growth.</h1>
          <p>From your first night without a newborn to your first morning dropping off a soon-to-be kindergartener. We grow with your family.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== QUICK-JUMP STRIP ========== -->
    <nav class="program-jump" aria-label="Jump to a program">
      <div class="container">
        <ul class="program-jump-list">
          <li><a href="#infant"><span class="program-jump-age">6 wks – 12 mo</span><span class="program-jump-name">Infant</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#toddler"><span class="program-jump-age">1 – 2 yrs</span><span class="program-jump-name">Toddler</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#twos"><span class="program-jump-age">2 – 3 yrs</span><span class="program-jump-name">Twos</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#preschool"><span class="program-jump-age">3 – 4 yrs</span><span class="program-jump-name">Preschool</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#pre-k"><span class="program-jump-age">4 – 5 yrs</span><span class="program-jump-name">Pre-K</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#school-age"><span class="program-jump-age">6 – 12 yrs</span><span class="program-jump-name">School Age</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- ========== INFANT CARE ========== -->
    <section class="section" id="infant">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="program-detail fade-in">
          <div class="program-detail-text">
            <span class="age-badge-lg">6 weeks – 12 months</span>
            <h2>Infant Care</h2>
            <p>The first year is the most tender one. Our infant room is designed for calm: soft light, quiet corners, and caregivers who nurture each baby's individual milestones rather than rushing a group timeline.</p>
            <ul class="curriculum-list">
              <li><strong>Ratios kept under the state minimum.</strong> We follow all state guidelines strictly.</li>
              <li><strong>Real-time updates.</strong> Notifications for feedings, diaper changes, nap times, daily activities, photos, and all the moments that matter most, via Brightwheel.</li>
              <li><strong>Parent-led scheduling.</strong> We follow your child's established routine for feedings, naps, and care whenever possible.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-outline-green mt-24">Tour the infant room &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="program-detail-img">
            <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder for infant room">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                <circle cx="24" cy="22" r="6" fill="#6CB43A" opacity="0.5"/>
                <path d="M14 38c0-5.5 4.5-10 10-10s10 4.5 10 10" stroke="#1F5247" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: infant room, natural light, primary caregiver with baby</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== TODDLER ========== -->
    <section class="section section-green-bg" id="toddler">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="program-detail reverse fade-in">
          <div class="program-detail-text">
            <span class="age-badge-lg">1 – 2 years</span>
            <h2>Toddler Program</h2>
            <p>Big feelings, little people, huge growth. Every interaction is a learning opportunity. Through talking, singing, reading aloud, and responsive conversations, we help toddlers develop confidence in communication and in understanding the world around them.</p>
            <ul class="curriculum-list">
              <li><strong>1:5 ratio.</strong> State ratios are taken seriously and followed strictly.</li>
              <li><strong>Sensory and outdoor play daily.</strong> Water tables, textures, music, secure outdoor space.</li>
              <li><strong>Language-rich classroom.</strong> Toddlers add roughly one new word per waking hour. We design around that.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-outline-green mt-24">Tour the toddler room &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="program-detail-img">
            <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder for toddler classroom">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                <rect x="14" y="20" width="20" height="16" rx="3" fill="#6CB43A" opacity="0.5"/>
                <circle cx="20" cy="14" r="3" fill="#1F5247"/>
                <circle cx="28" cy="14" r="3" fill="#1F5247"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: toddler classroom, sensory play in progress</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== TWO-YEAR-OLDS ========== -->
    <section class="section" id="twos">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="program-detail fade-in">
          <div class="program-detail-text">
            <span class="age-badge-lg">2 – 3 years</span>
            <h2>Two-Year-Olds</h2>
            <p>Our two-year-old classroom is a safe, nurturing, and engaging environment where children learn through play, exploration, and meaningful relationships. Daily routines provide consistency while encouraging independence, language, social skills, and early learning. Through hands-on activities, music, stories, sensory experiences, and learning centers, children build confidence, curiosity, and a lifelong love of learning.</p>
            <ul class="curriculum-list">
              <li><strong>Ratios: 1:8 (24–29 months), 1:9 (30–35 months).</strong> State ratios are taken seriously and followed strictly.</li>
              <li><strong>Sensory and outdoor play.</strong> Children explore, discover, and grow through daily sensory experiences and outdoor play.</li>
              <li><strong>Language-rich classroom.</strong> We build language skills through songs, stories, conversations, and play, helping children grow from single words to complete sentences and meaningful conversations.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-outline-green mt-24">Tour the two-year-old room &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="program-detail-img">
            <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder for two-year-old classroom">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                <rect x="10" y="26" width="10" height="10" rx="2" fill="#6CB43A" opacity="0.6"/>
                <rect x="22" y="26" width="10" height="10" rx="2" fill="#5FA8D3" opacity="0.6"/>
                <rect x="16" y="14" width="10" height="10" rx="2" fill="#EF9F27" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: two-year-old classroom, learning centers in use</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== PRESCHOOL ========== -->
    <section class="section section-green-bg" id="preschool">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="program-detail reverse fade-in">
          <div class="program-detail-text">
            <span class="age-badge-lg">3 – 4 years</span>
            <h2>Preschool</h2>
            <p>Great preschool isn't "kindergarten minus one year." It's its own developmental window. Our preschool classroom prepares children through hands-on learning, purposeful play, and meaningful experiences. We foster independence, confidence, early literacy and math skills, problem-solving, and social-emotional development in a caring, language-rich environment where every child is encouraged to explore, grow, and succeed.</p>
            <ul class="curriculum-list">
              <li><strong>1:11 ratio.</strong> Followed strictly.</li>
              <li><strong>Education.</strong> Our lesson plans provide engaging, developmentally appropriate learning through hands-on exploration and play.</li>
              <li><strong>Learning together.</strong> We balance small- and large-group activities to prepare children for the next step in education, while making sure each child gets the individualized support and attention they need to succeed.</li>
              <li><strong>Learning through choice.</strong> We encourage children to share their interests, then listen and weave them into lesson plans, keeping them engaged while exploring topics that spark curiosity and support meaningful learning.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-outline-green mt-24">Tour the preschool room &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="program-detail-img">
            <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder for preschool classroom">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                <polygon points="24,8 30,20 42,22 33,30 36,42 24,36 12,42 15,30 6,22 18,20" fill="#5FA8D3" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: preschool small-group station with teacher</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== PRE-K ========== -->
    <section class="section" id="pre-k">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="program-detail fade-in">
          <div class="program-detail-text">
            <span class="age-badge-lg">4 – 5 years</span>
            <h2>Pre-K</h2>
            <p>Ready for kindergarten, still in love with learning. Our Pre-K program balances structured learning with purposeful play, building strong foundations in literacy, math, science, social-emotional development, and problem-solving. Children leave with the confidence, independence, and school-ready skills they need for a successful start to kindergarten and everything after.</p>
            <ul class="curriculum-list">
              <li><strong>Ratios: 1:13.</strong> State minimum is 1:17.</li>
              <li><strong>Classroom schedule.</strong> Ample time for the skills that matter most for kindergarten, including literacy, math, and science.</li>
              <li><strong>Independence skills, practiced.</strong> We won't forget the life skills that are easy to take for granted, like eating lunch on their own, managing the bathroom, and even packing their own bag.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-outline-green mt-24">Tour the Pre-K room &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="program-detail-img">
            <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder for Pre-K classroom">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                <rect x="8" y="10" width="32" height="28" rx="3" fill="#EAF3F8" stroke="#2C6F95" stroke-width="2"/>
                <line x1="14" y1="18" x2="34" y2="18" stroke="#2C6F95" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="14" y1="24" x2="30" y2="24" stroke="#2C6F95" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="14" y1="30" x2="26" y2="30" stroke="#2C6F95" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: Pre-K classroom, child working independently at a table</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== SCHOOL AGE (coming soon) ========== -->
    <section class="section section-green-bg" id="school-age">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">School age &middot; 6 – 12 years</p>
          <h2>Summer and break care is on the way.</h2>
          <p>Care for school-age children during the summer and school breaks is coming to IGA. Check back in September for program details.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== SHARED FOUNDATION ========== -->
    <section class="section section-teal-bg">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">No matter the room</p>
          <h2>Every program, same foundation.</h2>
          <p>The IGA standards don't change between classrooms. These six commitments hold for infants and Pre-K alike.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="foundation-grid fade-in">
          <li>
            <h3>Degree-qualified lead teachers</h3>
            <p>Every classroom has a lead with a degree in early childhood education or child development.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Background-checked, trained support staff</h3>
            <p>Every adult in the building has cleared a background check and completed our onboarding training.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Ratios that follow state guidelines</h3>
            <p>We follow all state guidelines strictly, keeping classrooms small in every age group.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Locally sourced meals</h3>
            <p>Breakfast, lunch, and two snacks every day, including at least one hot meal. Allergen-aware, with fresh vegetables and fruit always on the menu, giving your child the nutrition to power a full day of play and learning.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Daily outdoor time</h3>
            <p>Weather permitting, we are outside every day. Winters included, layers required.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Real-time updates via Brightwheel</h3>
            <p>Photos, daily reports, and direct teacher messaging. No more wondering how the day went.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== DAILY RHYTHM ========== -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">Sample Tuesday</p>
          <h2>What a day at IGA looks like.</h2>
          <p>This is a typical preschool day. Infant, toddler, and two-year-old days have a gentler shape but follow the same philosophy: predictable rhythms, child-led moments, real learning throughout.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="daily-rhythm fade-in">
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">6:30 – 8:30 AM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Arrival, free play, breakfast</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">8:30 – 9:00 AM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Final drop-offs</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">9:00 – 9:15 AM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Morning circle: weather, story, daily question</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">9:15 – 10:15 AM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Curriculum time: rotating literacy, math, science, art</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">10:15 – 11:30 AM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Outdoor play and exploration</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">11:30 AM – 12:00 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Curriculum time</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">12:00 – 1:00 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Lunch and clean-up</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">1:00 – 3:00 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Rest or quiet activities</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">3:00 – 3:30 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Snack and project time</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">3:30 – 5:00 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Outdoor play, free choice</span></li>
          <li><span class="rhythm-time">5:00 – 6:00 PM</span><span class="rhythm-activity">Wind-down and goodbyes</span></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== CTA BAND ========== -->
    <section class="cta-band section-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <h2>Which program is right for your child?</h2>
          <p>The best way to find out is to see it in person. Tour the IGA campus nearest you, meet the teachers, watch how your child responds to the space.</p>
          <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Schedule a Free Tour</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>
